​Project Love: This initiative tackles clothing insecurity by supplying new clothing, undergarments, and shoes to children in crisis within the Clay County District Schools.  We work closely with school social workers and staff to ensure that children are able to fully engage in their education without the burden of inadequate clothing or shoes.

adx_publicprofilecopy:
There’s a reason we chose Lighthouse Coaching and Consulting as our name and the lighthouse as our icon. And honestly, it wasn’t some big marketing idea with a focus group. It just... clicked. Because the more you think about it, the more you realize it's a perfect metaphor for what we do.

Think about a ship lost at sea. The weather is rough, the fog is thick, and the captain has lost their bearings. The compass is spinning, and they're sailing blind. That feeling of being lost, of being overwhelmed by life's "storms," is something we all experience at some point.

Now, imagine that captain spotting a lighthouse. The lighthouse doesn’t suddenly jump on board and start steering the ship for them. It doesn’t scream commands or tell them exactly what to do. The lighthouse simply stands firm, a constant, steady beacon of light. It shows the captain where the shore is, where the dangerous rocks are, and, most importantly, it reminds them that there is a path forward. The light illuminates the possibilities, but the captain is the one who ultimately charts the course.

That’s exactly what we do. You are the captain of your own life. Your ship is your career, your relationships, your health, your well-being. We’re not here to take the helm. We're here to be your lighthouse—a firm, guiding presence that provides clarity and direction when you feel lost. We help you cut through the fog of confusion, identify the hidden rocks of self-doubt, and find your true north.

The goal of our coaching isn’t for you to follow our light forever. It's to help you find and strengthen your own inner light, so you can confidently navigate any sea you encounter, no matter how stormy. That's what makes the lighthouse such a fitting icon for us. It’s a symbol of hope, clarity, and the power of finding your way home.

We bring nonprofits, businesses, faith groups, and local government together and run hands-on programs: mobile neighborhood care (Impact Clay Train), countywide disaster recovery (Recovering Clay), low-cost nonprofit workspace (Professional Center), shared community projects (Project Partners), leadership training (Global Leadership Summit), and a real-time resource platform (Linksy). Our collaborative efforts aim to build a stronger, more resilient Clay County where everyone can enjoy an improved quality of life. Explore our programs to find services or ways to get involved.

Emmanuel Project of Northeast Florida, is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit mobile medical clinic dedicated to delivering high-quality, no-cost healthcare services to provide healthcare access to rural communities and care for uninsured children, adults, working families, and the underserved communities across Northeast Florida.
Healthcare is a fundamental human right, yet for many in Northeast Florida, it remains out of reach. We believe that no one should have to choose between putting food on the table and seeing a doctor. We do not have a brick and mortar which allows us to focus on patients where they live. We cross county lines and travel many miles to bridge this divide by bringing compassionate, quality medical care directly to those who need it most, regardless of their ability to pay or where they live. We operate without billing patients. Instead we are offering them a healthy head start and a chance to focus on their health instead of the medical debt. 
Our services encompass primary care, pediatrics, preventive care, chronic disease management, health education, mental fitness services, and community outreach. Our mission is rooted in a deep commitment to provide compassionate care to those too often overlooked. We serve a diverse patient population, including children, adults, ALICE (Asset Limited, Income Constrained, Employed) households.
